{"ts":"2026-03-06T04:55:04Z","cmd":"git add config/initializers/middleware_ruby31_fix.rb && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nFix build: patch middleware stack for Ruby 3.0+ keyword args\n\nRuby 3.0+ separates keyword arguments from positional arguments.\nThe middleware stack stores kwargs as a trailing hash in args array,\nthen splats them as positional args in #build, causing\n\"wrong number of arguments (given 3, expected 2)\" in\nActionDispatch::Static#initialize.\n\nMonkey-patch Middleware#build to detect trailing hash and pass it\nas **kwargs instead.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\" && git push origin master"}
